addition_note: Communal taxes are levied at rates varying from 0% to 9% of the income tax due
Except in Quebec, provincial and territorial taxes are calculated on the federal return and collected by the federal government.
The base on which surtax is calculated is the amount of tax liability
Income basis is personal income, instead of taxable income
The TCTS rate is 5% of the salary, indemnities, and emoluments paid to the taxpayer.
General income tax has distinct formula
The surtax is comprised of a 2.1% tax that is assessed on an individual’s national income tax
Individuals who derive in a tax year income exceeding PLN 1 million are required to pay solidarity tax at the rate of 4% on the excess of this amount.
In 2023, an additional solidarity rate, which varies between 2.5% and 5%, applies to taxpayers with a taxable income exceeding EUR 80,000.
This tax is 5% of the excess of the total net taxable income over USD 500,000, limited to 33% of their personal and dependents' exemption plus USD 8,895.

For general taxable income, progressive tax rates are applied (which are the sum of the applicable rate approved by the state and the applicable rate approved by each autonomous community of Spain in their progressive tax rate scales).
For the additional municipal taxes, the above rate has to be multiplied by the respective municipal tax factor, which varies between 0.75 and 1.34 (City of Zurich: 1.19).
